  "texts": [
    "As recommended in the COMET handbook, the nominal group technique, a highly structured group interaction framework, will be utilised to aid this process [16,17].",
    "Following a brief introduction and explanation of the purpose of the meeting by the facilitators, participants will discuss the inclusion and exclusion of candidate items and share any comments until all contributions are exhausted.",
    "This discussion phase will be led by the facilitators to ensure that the discussion will not be dominated by any one individual and be as neutral as possible [18].The first two rounds of the modified Delphi consensus process will be conducted as online surveys using the DelphiManager software (version 4.0), which is developed and maintained by the COMET (Core Outcome Measures in Effectiveness Trials) initiative.",
    "The final meeting to draft the QUADAS-AI tool will be conducted using Zoom.",
    "All data is pseudo-anonymised and no identifiable data will be published."
  ],
